<div id="review_3420273610" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3420273610" />
    <a title="Uptown Horror Reviews" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/102686222-uptown-horror-reviews"><img alt="Uptown Horror Reviews" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1617275355p2/102686222.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3420273610?book_show_action=true">Jun 16, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Uptown Horror Reviews" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Uptown Horror Reviews" href="/user/show/102686222-uptown-horror-reviews">Uptown Horror Reviews</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/102686222-uptown-horror-reviews?shelf=bizarro">bizarro</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/102686222-uptown-horror-reviews?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/102686222-uptown-horror-reviews?shelf=portal-horror">portal-horror</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3420273610" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5222884683025598942">After a series of strange events, Jamie is forced to join an interdimensional travelling circus and is forced to perform as a clown against his will. He is determined to escape this colorful prison, but there&apos;s one small problem holding him back: whenever he puts on his clown make-up for a performance he transforms into JJ The Clown - a demented, evil and mean-spirited version of Jim Carrey&apos;s &quot;The Mask&quot;. <br/><br/>The book then becomes a Jekyll and Hyde story as Jamie and JJ The Clown fight over control o</span>
  <span id="freeText5222884683025598942" style="display:none">After a series of strange events, Jamie is forced to join an interdimensional travelling circus and is forced to perform as a clown against his will. He is determined to escape this colorful prison, but there's one small problem holding him back: whenever he puts on his clown make-up for a performance he transforms into JJ The Clown - a demented, evil and mean-spirited version of Jim Carrey's "The Mask". <br /><br />The book then becomes a Jekyll and Hyde story as Jamie and JJ The Clown fight over control of their shared body. Jamie will stop at nothing to overthrow the oppressive regime who are running the Circus while JJ wants nothing more than to wreak havoc upon the world and sabotage all of Jamie's plans.<br /><br />The book was a breath of fresh air and although the page count was way longer than what Im used to, I didnt want it to end.<br /><br />Im giving this book 4 out of 5 stars ⭐⭐⭐⭐</span>
  <a data-text-id="5222884683025598942" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


